[{"id":"FT577877","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a circuit with a battery, a closed switch, two resistors, and a capacitor. The left side of the circuit has a battery labeled script e. Moving up the left side and across the top of the circuit, there is a closed switch labeled S and a resistor labeled R sub 1. To the right of the resistor, the circuit splits into two vertical branches. The first branch has a resistor labeled R sub 2, and the second branch has a capacitor labeled C. \" height=\"98\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/f4da7942e9458de6470083ec6749a18f/original.png\" width=\"250\" />\n<p>The circuit shown above includes a battery, two resistors, and a capacitor with values as labeled. The current through the battery is I. Which of the following is a correct equation for potential differences in the circuit a long time after the switch is closed?</p>\n","choicesHtml":["<em>ε</em> − <em>IR</em><sub>1</sub> − <em>IR</em><sub>2</sub> = 0","<em>ε</em> +<em> IR</em><sub>1</sub> +<em> IR</em><sub>2</sub> = 0","<em>ε</em> − <em>IR</em><sub>1</sub> − <em>IR</em><sub>2</sub> − <em>Cε</em> = 0","<em>ε </em>− <em>IR</em><sub>1</sub> − <em>IR</em><sub>2</sub> + <em>Cε</em> = 0"],"answer":-1}]